Brazil Forecasts 8.5 Billion Reais of Power-Line Investments

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-03-24T20:55:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/brazil-forecasts-8-5-billion-reais-of-power-line-investments.html
Brazil ’s government plans to
auction licenses for electricity-transmission projects expected
to attract 8.5 billion reais ($5.13 billion) of investments in
the next five years, the government’s energy research agency
said.  The investments will be made through 2015, the agency known
as EPE said today in an  e-mailed  statement. Spending may surpass
8.5 billion reais once lines connecting the Belo Monte
hydroelectric dam in the Amazon and the Teles Pires dam are
included, EPE said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 